comments: LeVert (CLE) does not step out of bounds while in possession of the ball.
Tatum (BOS) brings his hand across Garland's (CLE) front and the contact affects Garland's SQBR at the start of his drive.
Brown (BOS) brings his forearm to rest on Allen's (CLE) side and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) makes contact with the ball while it is still in the imaginary cylinder above the rim.
Allen's (CLE) forearm comes to rest on Porzingis' (BOS) side, and the contact during his drive is marginal.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: Allen (CLE) is the last player to touch the ball before the ball goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Celtics.
Niang (CLE) rests his arm on Porzingis' (BOS) side and marginal contact occurs as the two move in the same direction off-ball.
Niang (CLE) is moving alongside Tatum's (BOS) path and marginal contact occurs on the perimeter.
Allen (CLE) firms up over his right leg and absorbs the contact from Holiday (BOS) to his upper body.
Porzingis (BOS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Allen (CLE), and the ensuing body contact is incidental.
Garland (CLE) swipes his arm down and makes contact with Porzingis' (BOS) arms as he defends the shot near the rim.
Porzingis (BOS) moves alongside Garland's (CLE) path and absorbs the marginal contact as Garland cuts toward the opposite side of the basket.
Garland (CLE) grasps and immediately releases White's (BOS) jersey as they disengage during the pick.
White (BOS) establishes himself in Allen's (CLE) path and the contact that occurs during the pick is marginal.
Niang (CLE) is in the paint for three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Garland (CLE) brings his forearm towards Tatum's (BOS) front, and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Tatum (BOS) is bracing for the contact from Garland (CLE), and marginal contact occurs as he releases away.

Replay review of the foul called on Garland (CLE) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed successful. Garland closes out in front of Tatum (BOS) and avoids making contact during the release of his jump shot attempt. After the release, marginal lower body contact occurs with Tatum's partially extended right leg. Additionally - the contact from Tatum's right leg does not take Garland out of the play, and neither an offensive nor a shooting foul are warranted. Neither team is in imminent possession of the ball at the time of the whistle and play correctly resumes with a jump ball at center circle.
The game clock expires as White (BOS) secures possession, and Coach Mazulla (BOS) signals for a timeout after the game has ended.
